00:00:00.850 --> 00:00:03.970
&gt;&gt; The Library of Congress
in Washington DC.

00:00:22.700 --> 00:00:25.300
&gt;&gt; Mary-Jane Deeb: Welcome
to Library of Congress.

00:00:25.300 --> 00:00:30.110
I am Mary-Jane Deeb, Chief of the
African and Middle Eastern Division

00:00:30.110 --> 00:00:33.980
and I wish you all a happy Nowruz.

00:00:33.980 --> 00:00:40.870
We are celebrating today Nowruz
with a special cultural program

00:00:40.870 --> 00:00:52.100 position:56%
on Azerbaijani culture and food, and
I just want to say that every year,

00:00:52.100 --> 00:00:59.650
the African and Middle Eastern
division, which is responsible

00:00:59.650 --> 00:01:04.800
for the collections and for
serving those collections

00:01:04.800 --> 00:01:15.770
from 78 different countries
is here and collects materials

00:01:15.770 --> 00:01:18.100
from Azerbaijan that
it serves, as well.

00:01:18.100 --> 00:01:21.080
Now why we celebrate Nowruz,

00:01:21.080 --> 00:01:27.520 position:56%
it is because it is a secular
facility sacred to the Zoroastrians,

00:01:27.520 --> 00:01:34.460
but in fact, celebrated not
only in Iran, the Persian world,

00:01:34.460 --> 00:01:40.430
the Persian speaking world, but
also throughout central Asia

00:01:40.430 --> 00:01:44.830
from Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan,
Uzbekistan,

00:01:44.830 --> 00:01:49.560
and certainly in Azerbaijan.

00:01:49.560 --> 00:01:56.750
It is also celebrated in India,
and in some of the people in Iraq

00:01:56.750 --> 00:02:01.280
and Turkey, in Turkmenistan,
and many other places.

00:02:01.280 --> 00:02:03.780
And every year, we
do something special.

00:02:03.780 --> 00:02:10.480
So this is a very special
event today 2016, for example,

00:02:10.480 --> 00:02:13.000 position:56%
we celebrated it at the White House.

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:17.040
We were invited by Mrs.
Obama, and we had a display

00:02:17.040 --> 00:02:22.260
and a special Nowruz lunch
at the White House in 2015.

00:02:22.260 --> 00:02:27.330
We had a special presentation
by Dr. Saeed Hussein Nasser,

00:02:27.330 --> 00:02:30.180
and many of you know him
at George Washington.

00:02:30.180 --> 00:02:39.050
In 2014, we opened a big exhibit
on 1000 years of the Persian book.

00:02:39.050 --> 00:02:44.990
A year earlier, we had a
film on the Shah Hanami.

00:02:44.990 --> 00:02:53.930
So year after year, we have unique
programs that celebrate new year,

00:02:53.930 --> 00:02:56.350
celebrate the beginning of spring.

00:02:56.350 --> 00:02:59.600
I know it's a not very
auspicious the snow outside,

00:02:59.600 --> 00:03:06.570
but we do what we can to
bring spring to everyone

00:03:06.570 --> 00:03:11.990
and to bring spring through
Nowruz, through the programs,

00:03:11.990 --> 00:03:15.430
through the food, through
the culture, which is so rich

00:03:15.430 --> 00:03:19.780
and so wonderful, and you
hear much more about it today.

00:03:19.780 --> 00:03:26.070
We are delighted to be cosponsoring
this event today with the embassy

00:03:26.070 --> 00:03:31.890
